title: Taking Ownership of our Expertise
description: Taking Ownership of our Expertise is about demystifying Impostor Syndrome and tips to step up & own our expertise!.

title: The Art of Storytelling with Data Science
description: In a rapidly expanding field like data science, with data everywhere, it’s easy to merely focus on technical skills: coding, data types, algorithms. It’s quintessential to make data consumable for the business, explore promising tools and skills towards creating human-centered data science and speculate future directions for data analytics and visualizations. This talk will throw light on how data helps businesses solve problems worth millions and have tangible outcomes, roadmap to visualizations and best practices of storytelling with data!

title: Learn to Write, Write to Learn
description: Every engineer is also a writer, but you don't need to be an engineer to write. The workshop aims to guide and demystify some common misconceptions around content writing. Learn whom to write for and what to write for them by understanding what your audience might like to read. More importantly, this is a motivation to conquer the writer's block. Also its not just about writing, you will also gain some tips on how you can turn writing into a career.

title: Enhance your Core Web Vitals with AMP
description: This talk covers the unified guidance for quality signals & the metrics that are essential to delivering a great user experience on the web and helps the developer in making performant solutions for the users. It will also throw some light on the best practices and performance with Accelerated Mobile Pages (AMP).

title: Product Management from my lens
description: The talk is a candid primer on a career in Product Management and busts some common myths around it. Through some insightful case studies, I also touch upon what it takes to build great products.

title: Named Entity Recognition with Tensorflow
description: Building and training a custom deep-learning NER model with Tensorflow and deploying it as a REST API.

title: Architecture Before Code
description: We will look at the importance of Architecture and why it is important to choose the right architecture before starting to code. We will deep dive into a few different architecture patterns and their real life applications.

title: The Power of a Good Portfolio
description: CVs are so old school. Portfolios, on the other hand, will help you stand out from the crowd, show your uniqueness, and build trust. Here's all you need to know about the unique way of showcasing your work.

title: You can help your children to Live life by their design and Grow together
description: In session I will discussing about the Mindset, Skills and Tools essential for one to Live life by their design. How parents and children can grow together?.

title: Little known facts about Speech Technology
description: I'll explain how modern Speech systems work and share interesting facts about Speech Technology. See also my older blog post https://towardsdatascience.com/little-known-facts-about-speech-technology-497e5ea47e56

title: Reframing your Narrative
description: This talk is about demystifying Impostor Syndrome and tips to step up & own our expertise!

title: Enhancing Core Web Vitals with AMP
description: Enhancing Core Web Vitals with AMP

title: Building apps by leveraging external APIs
description: An API is a way of communication between two or more applications, we'll be talking about first and third party APIs and how we can leverage such pre-made ready to use interfaces for building apps on top of them to make something extraordinary!

title: Paving the way for the next generation
description: How do you fight for getting a seat at the table in your field? How do you make your voice heard? How do you make an impactful contribution to your field? This talk covers the life stories of three prominent Indian women scientists who paved the way and showed us how to do it.
